							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/jenbenka/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Jen-Benka-photo_Credit-Carol-Mirakove-scaled-e1731090507348-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Jen-Benka-photo_Credit-Carol-Mirakove-scaled-e1731090507348-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Jen Benka" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/jenbenka/">Jen Benka</a></h6>
										Jen Benka is the author of two books of poems and numerous essays. An arts & culture worker, Benka recently served as the President & Executive Director of the Academy of American Poets, the publisher of Poets.org, and received the Pegasus Award for Service in Poetry.																			</div>
